title: For Sale/Trade:  12 gauge BPS - great condition
postcontent: the title pretty much says it all, but in case you are not familiar with this great firearm, let me catch you up to speed. Browning, of course, makes some of the finest guns on the market today. The BPS is a unique shotgun on today's market because it is a bottom eject gun. title: For Sale:  100 year old Colt 1911 and rig
location: N.E. Metro, Minneapolis / St. Paul, Minnesota
postcontent: WWI Colt "Black Army" 1911 marked “US Property”.This Colt Model of 1911 has a 440K serial number and dates to 1918.  It is referred to as a "Black Army" because of what was originally a crude, brushed blued finish during late WWI production.  It has "AA" markings which indicate an "Augusta Arsenal" overhaul sometime after 1918.  Likely this is where the arched mainspring housing was installed and the GI plastic grips took the place of the original wood grips.  Sometime after separating from service, the family of the vet tells me their dad decided to have the slide and frame hot-blued.  The barrel (marked "P" and "H" on the chamber hood) is in excellent original condition and did not get refinished.Other than the mainspring housing and plastic grips, all other parts appear to be original WWI Colt production.  Though many exterior markings are faint, they are all present and the pistol shoots reliably and quite accurately despite the very fine early 1911 sights.I've got several accessories that should stay with the pistol.  They are all GI but were WWII issue.  Includes:1942 Boyt GI flapped holster in excellent condition3 GI 1911 magazines (one marked "L")Canvass GI 1911 double magazine pouch1911 WWII shoulder holster that has a very "been there, done that" field maintained appeal. $1400 for all.15 minutes north of downtown St. Paul.
